items.text: SEE GENERAL NOTES SHEET FOR ADDITIONAL GENERAL NOTES & INFORMATION.
FIELD VERIFY ALL ELEVATIONS SHOWN WHERE PROPOSED IMPROVEMENTS ABUT
EXISTING IMPROVEMENTS PRIOR TO CONSTRUCTION. IMMEDIATELY NOTIFY PROJECT
EXISTING UTILITIES WHETHER SHOWN OR NOT, SHALL BE PROTECTED IN PLACE,
UNLESS OTHERWISE NOTED. ACCESS BOXES SHALL BE ADJUSTED TO GRADE.
CONTRACTOR SHALL REMOVE & DISPOSE OF ALL EXISTING CONCRETE
IMPROVEMENTS NECESSARY TO INSTALL NEW IMPROVEMENTS. ANY CONCRETE (I.E.
SIDEWALK OR CURB & GUTTER) DAMAGED OR REMOVED, AS NECESSARY, FOR
CONSTRUCTION OF THE STORM DRAIN INLET SHALL BE INCLUDED IN THE
CONTRACTORS UNIT PRICE FOR EACH INLET.
EXISTING UTILITY LOCATIONS ARE FROM TOPOGRAPHIC SURVEY DATA & RECORDED
DATA. EXISTING GAS MAINS ARE ASSUMED TO HAVE 3' COVER FROM TOP OF
PAVEMENT. ALL DEPTHS SHOWN ARE ESTIMATED. CONTRACTOR SHALL NOTIFY
PROJECT ENGINEER IMMEDIATELY OF ANY DISCREPANCIES.
ALL UTILITY CROSSINGS SHOWN ON THE PLANS AND AS MARKED OUT BY THE
UNDERGROUND SERVICE ALERT (USA) SHALL BE PROTECTED IN PLACE.
CONTRACTOR SHALL REPLACE ALL STRIPING DAMAGE DURING CONSTRUCTION. SEE
STORM DRAIN PIPE SHALL BE INSTALLED IN ACCORDNACE WITH MANUFACTURER'S
RECOMMENDATIONS AND ADHERE TO THE CITY OF DINUBA STANDARDS.
CONTRACTOR SHALL USE A DRESSER COUPLING WHEN CONNECTING TO THE
EXISTING WATER SERVICE IF THE WATER SERVICE IS CTS POLYETHYLENE. IF THE
PIPE IS ANYTHING BUT CTS POLYETHYLENE, CONTRACTOR SHALL REPLACE THE
ENTIRE WATER SERVICE TO THE METER BOX.
GAS MAINS ARE SHOWN BASED ON SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA GAS COMPANY PLAT
MAPS GAS MAIN LOCATION AND DEPTH WERE NOT POSITIVELY VERIFIED.
RESIDENTS SHALL HAVE ACCESS TO WATER FROM 3:30 PM UNTIL 8:00 AM.
CONCRETE IMPROVEMENTS DAMAGED DURING CONSTRUCTION SHALL BE
RECONSTRUCTED PER CITY OF DINUBA STANDARDS.
THE SANITARY SEWER SERVICES SHOWN ON THE PLANS ARE APPROXIMATE.
CONTRACTOR SHALL ENSURE EVERYTHING IS CONNECTED APPROPRIATELY.
